RULES:
1. This project is a Mini-ERP for a university laboratory called LabGFHA
2. Tech stack: Next.js 14+ App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, Supabase
3. Always use the Supabase clients from /lib/supabase/ — never create new clients
4. Always validate inputs with Zod schemas from /lib/validators/
5. Always use TypeScript types from /lib/types/
6. Never modify the folder structure without explicit approval
7. Never change CSS framework — stay on Tailwind + shadcn/ui
8. Business logic goes in /lib/business-logic/, never in components
9. Every page must handle 3 states: loading (skeleton), error (message), empty (empty state)
10. Use the Stitch MCP server to pull designs for each page before implementing
11. The Supabase database is already created with all tables, RLS policies, triggers and seed data
12. Always commit after each functional component or page